11 SECTION 3. IC 16-18-2-1, AS AMENDED BY P.L.136-2013,
12 SECTION 1, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
13 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 1. "Abortion" means the termination of human
14 pregnancy with an intention other than to produce a live birth or to
15 remove a dead fetus. The term includes abortions by surgical
16 procedures and by abortion inducing drugs. act of using or
17 prescribing an instrument, a drug, a medicine, or any other
18 substance, device, or means with the intent to cause the death of an
19 unborn child of a woman. The term does not include birth control
20 devices or contraceptives. An act is not an abortion if the act is
21 done with the intent to:
22 (1) save the life or preserve the health of an unborn child;
23 (2) remove a dead, unborn child whose death was caused by
24 miscarriage or stillbirth; or
25 (3) remove an ectopic pregnancy.
