10 SECTION 18. IC 34-13-9-0.7, AS ADDED BY P.L.4-2015,
11 SECTION 1, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
12 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 0.7. This chapter does not:
13 (1) authorize a provider to refuse to offer or provide services,
14 facilities, use of public accommodations, goods, employment, or
15 housing to any member or members of the general public on the
16 basis of race, color, religion, ancestry, age, national origin,
17 disability, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, or United
18 States military service;
19 (2) establish a defense to a civil action or criminal prosecution for
20 refusal by a provider to offer or provide services, facilities, use of
21 public accommodations, goods, employment, or housing to any
22 member or members of the general public on the basis of race,
23 color, religion, ancestry, age, national origin, disability, sex,
24 sexual orientation, gender identity, or United States military
25 service; or
26 (3) limit or curtail the scope of any law of the state of Indiana
27 that regulates or restricts abortion or that withholds taxpayer
28 funds from entities that perform or promote abortions; or
29 (3) (4) negate any rights available under the Constitution of the
30 State of Indiana.
31 SECTION 19. IC 34-13-9-2, AS ADDED BY P.L.3-2015,
32 SECTION 1, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
33 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 2. (a) A governmental entity statute, ordinance,
34 resolution, executive or administrative order, regulation, custom, or
35 usage may not be construed to be exempt from the application of this
36 chapter unless a state statute expressly exempts the statute, ordinance,
37 resolution, executive or administrative order, regulation, custom, or
38 usage from the application of this chapter by citation to this chapter.
39 (b) This chapter does not apply to IC 16-34 or any action to
40 enforce the requirements of IC 16-34.
