1 [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 218.5. IC 16-34-7-21 (Concerning
2 abortion inducing drugs).
3 SECTION 21. IC 35-46-5-1.5, AS ADDED BY P.L.213-2016,
4 SECTION 30, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
5 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 1.5. (a) As used in this section, "aborted" means
6 the termination of human pregnancy with an intention other than to
7 produce a live birth or to remove a dead fetus. The term includes
8 abortions by surgical procedures and by abortion inducing drugs in
9 violation of IC 16-34-7.
10 (b) As used in this section, "fetal tissue" includes tissue, organs, or
11 any other part of an aborted fetus.
12 (c) This section does not apply to the proper medical disposal of
13 fetal tissue.
14 (d) A person who intentionally acquires, receives, sells, or transfers
15 fetal tissue commits unlawful transfer of fetal tissue, a Level 5 felony.
16 (e) A person may not alter the timing, method, or procedure used to
17 terminate a pregnancy for the purpose of obtaining or collecting fetal
18 tissue. A person who violates this subsection commits the unlawful
19 collection of fetal tissue, a Level 5 felony.
